  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nIn Join public chat screen user types \"A\" in topic. After this \r\n* all other typed characters are not shown at all (on iOS) \r\n* next typed character \"deletes\" the first one so field is empty (on Android)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nIf there is any restriction then user should get a feedback from the app about it or typed uppercase character should be transformed to lowercase. If user types some allowed characters then they should be shown in the topic field.\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nUser types \"A\" and it's shown in the topic field. Than type \"m\":\r\n1. on iOS it's not shown, so field contains \"A\"\r\n2. on Android field becomes empty\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nvideo (Android): https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7QkFCRUNabElMc2M\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Chats\r\n- tap on +\r\n- tap Join public chat\r\n- set keyboard to uppercase and type \"A\"\r\n- type \"m\". check that topic field contains \"Am\" or \"am\". \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.8 and 0.9.9 and 0.9.7\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device Samsung Galaxy S6, Android 6.0.1\r\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOS 10.2.1\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
